<subSubSection id="ACE5C4C3FFCEFFA0AD3DB925FD1AFC9F" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="98" pageId="14" pageNumber="97" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="E4409748FFCEFFA1AD3DB925FF4DF9F0" blockId="14.[113,646,1610,1700]" box="[113,213,1610,1636]" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E4409748FFCEFFA0AD3DB905FD1AFC9F" blockId="14.[113,646,1610,1700]" lastBlockId="15.[111,648,470,781]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="98" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">
Before description of new taxa allied to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFCEFFA1AD3FB9E5FF75F936" authorityName="H. Adams &amp; A. Adams" authorityYear="1858" box="[115,237,1674,1700]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Ctenocardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="14" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCEFFA1AD3FB9E5FF75F936" box="[115,237,1674,1700]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">Ctenocardia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can occur, a brief discussion concerning the genus and closely similar genera is necessary,as the genus 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFCEFFA1AFABBE99FCFAFD82" authorityName="H. Adams &amp; A. Adams" authorityYear="1858" box="[743,866,502,528]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Ctenocardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="14" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCEFFA1AFABBE99FCFAFD82" box="[743,866,502,528]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">Ctenocardia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, like all 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFCEFFA1AEF5BE99FB8EFD82" authorityName="Stewart" authorityYear="1930" box="[953,1046,502,528]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="14" pageNumber="104" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Fraginae">Fraginae</taxonomicName>
, has never been formally revised.Although the original description by H. Adams &amp; A. 
<bibRefCitation id="806EEAB9FFCEFFA1AE01BD5AFC7CFDDD" author="ADAMS H. &amp; ADAMS A." box="[845,996,565,591]" pageId="14" pageNumber="97" refId="ref16687" refString="ADAMS H. &amp; ADAMS A. 1858. - The Genera of Recent Mollusca: Arranged According to their Organization. Vol. II. John van Voorst, London, 661 p." type="book" year="1858">Adams (1858)</bibRefCitation>
is brief, 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFCEFFA1A972BD5AFB22FDDD" authorityName="H. Adams &amp; A. Adams" authorityYear="1858" box="[1086,1210,565,591]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Ctenocardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="14" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCEFFA1A972BD5AFB22FDDD" box="[1086,1210,565,591]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">Ctenocardia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first recognized as distinct from other cardiids due to a heart-shaped form, an abruptly truncate anterior, a carinate beak and spinose ribs, this latter character being the main character differentiating the genus from other subfamily members. Much later, 
<bibRefCitation id="806EEAB9FFCEFFA1AF92BD9CFCFCFC9F" author="HABE T." box="[734,868,755,781]" pageId="14" pageNumber="97" refId="ref16947" refString="HABE T. 1951. - [Genera of Japanese Shells. Pelecypoda and Scaphopoda]. Volume 2. Kairui-Bunken-Kankokai, Kyoto, 326 p. (in Japanese)." type="book" year="1951">Habe (1951)</bibRefCitation>
described the genus 
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCEFFA1A979BD9CFB21FC9F" box="[1077,1209,755,781]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">Microfragum</emphasis>
as having a small, flabelliform shell, with a more or less lobate posterior margin, not noticeably convex and without spikes on the radial ribs. This genus was erected in order to differentiate the 
<typeStatus id="3B4429EAFFCEFFA1A9C0BC1DFB22FC1E" box="[1164,1210,882,908]" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFCEFFA1AFB2BCFDFBEFFC39" authority="Deshayes, 1855" authorityName="Deshayes" authorityYear="1855" box="[766,1143,913,940]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Cardium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="14" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="festivum">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCEFFA1AFB2BCFDFC26FC3E" box="[766,958,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">Cardium festivum</emphasis>
Deshayes, 1855
</taxonomicName>
, from other members of the subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFCEFFA1AEBFBCDEFBC8FC59" authorityName="Stewart" authorityYear="1930" box="[1011,1104,945,971]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="14" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Fraginae">Fraginae</taxonomicName>
.However, similarities among some members of 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFCEFFA1A95BBCBEFB16FC79" authorityName="H. Adams &amp; A. Adams" authorityYear="1858" box="[1047,1166,977,1003]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Ctenocardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="14" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCEFFA1A95BBCBEFB16FC79" box="[1047,1166,977,1003]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">Ctenocardia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCEFFA1AFE8BC9EFCB2FB99" box="[676,810,1009,1035]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">Microfragum</emphasis>
were evident and first recognized by 
<bibRefCitation id="806EEAB9FFCEFFA1AFEABB7FFCD4FBB8" author="PRASHAD B." box="[678,844,1040,1066]" pageId="14" pageNumber="97" refId="ref17480" refString="PRASHAD B. 1932. - The Lamellibranchia of the Siboga Expedition. Systematic Part II. Pelecypoda (exclusive of the Pectinidae). Brill, Leiden, 353 p." type="book" year="1932">Prashad (1932)</bibRefCitation>
. Although 
<bibRefCitation id="806EEAB9FFCEFFA1AE8FBB7FFBFEFBB8" author="PRASHAD B." box="[963,1126,1040,1066]" pageId="14" pageNumber="97" refId="ref17480" refString="PRASHAD B. 1932. - The Lamellibranchia of the Siboga Expedition. Systematic Part II. Pelecypoda (exclusive of the Pectinidae). Brill, Leiden, 353 p." type="book" year="1932">Prashad (1932)</bibRefCitation>
did not include 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFCEFFA1AFBABB5FFCF4FBD8" authorityName="Deshayes" authorityYear="1855" box="[758,876,1072,1098]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Cardium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="14" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="festivum">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCEFFA1AFBABB5FFC96FBD8" box="[758,782,1072,1098]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCEFFA1AE55BB5FFCF4FBD8" box="[793,876,1072,1098]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">festivum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFCEFFA1A958BB5FFB15FBD8" authorityName="H. Adams &amp; A. Adams" authorityYear="1858" box="[1044,1165,1072,1098]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Ctenocardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="14" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCEFFA1A958BB5FFB15FBD8" box="[1044,1165,1072,1098]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">Ctenocardia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the form and general facies of 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFCEFFA1AEFDBB3FFBB1FBF8" authorityName="Deshayes" authorityYear="1855" box="[945,1065,1103,1130]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Cardium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="14" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="festivum">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCEFFA1AEFDBB3FFC51FBF8" box="[945,969,1104,1130]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCEFFA1AE99BB3FFBB1FBF8" box="[981,1065,1104,1130]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">festivum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were noted as similar to 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFCEFFA1AE4ABB00FD45FB3B" authority="Sowerby, 1841" authorityName="Sowerby" authorityYear="1841" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Cardium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="14" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="fornicatum" subGenus="Ctenocardia">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCEFFA1AE4ABB00FCF8FB1B" box="[774,864,1135,1161]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">Cardium</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCEFFA1AE21BB00FC7AFB1B" box="[877,994,1135,1161]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">Ctenocardia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCEFFA1AEA3BB00FBC3FB1B" box="[1007,1115,1135,1161]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">fornicatum</emphasis>
Sowerby, 1841
</taxonomicName>
. After examination of the 
<typeStatus id="3B4429EAFFCEFFA1AEB4BBE0FBBEFB3B" box="[1016,1062,1167,1193]" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">type</typeStatus>
specimens of both genera by us, it is clear that these taxa share many shell features in common, yet are still distinct. The rib lamellae though similar to other members of 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFCEFFA1AF8CBA61FCA4FABA" authorityName="H. Adams &amp; A. Adams" authorityYear="1858" box="[704,828,1294,1320]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Ctenocardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="14" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCEFFA1AF8CBA61FCA4FABA" box="[704,828,1294,1320]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">Ctenocardia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in being “mosaistracal” (
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCEFFA1A90EBA61FBEDFABA" box="[1090,1141,1294,1320]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="806EEAB9FFCEFFA1A937BA61FD45FAD5" author="VOKES H. E." pageId="14" pageNumber="97" pagination="143 - 189" refId="ref18635" refString="VOKES H. E. 1977. - Cardiidae (Mollusca: Bivalvia) from the Chipola Formation, Calhoun County, Florida. Tulane Studies in Geology and Paleontology 13: 143 - 189." type="journal article" year="1977">Vokes 1977</bibRefCitation>
) in nature, are distinct in being less spinose, thinner and more flattened and serried.Similarly, the somewhat quadrate and keeled gross shell shape,most pronounced in juvenile specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFCEFFA1A96ABAE3FB06FA34" authorityName="Deshayes" authorityYear="1855" box="[1062,1182,1420,1446]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Cardium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="14" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="festivum">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCEFFA1A96ABAE3FB06FA34" box="[1062,1182,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">M. festivum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is reminiscent of other 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFCEFFA1AE3ABAC3FC76FA54" authorityName="H. Adams &amp; A. Adams" authorityYear="1858" box="[886,1006,1452,1478]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Ctenocardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="14" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCEFFA1AE3ABAC3FC76FA54" box="[886,1006,1452,1478]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">Ctenocardia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
members, but adult 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFCEFFA1AFEEBAA3FCBBFA74" authorityName="Deshayes" authorityYear="1855" box="[674,803,1484,1510]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Cardium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="14" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="festivum">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCEFFA1AFEEBAA3FD23FA74" box="[674,699,1484,1510]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCEFFA1AF81BAA3FCBBFA74" box="[717,803,1484,1510]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">festivum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are less keeled and more flabelliform (although see 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFCEFFA1AE75BA83FB1AF997" authority="(Prashad, 1932))" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Prashad" baseAuthorityYear="1932" box="[825,1154,1515,1542]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Ctenocardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="14" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="translatum">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCEFFA1AE75BA83FC5FF994" box="[825,967,1516,1542]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">C. translatum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="806EEAB9FFCEFFA1AE9ABA84FBE8F997" author="PRASHAD B." box="[982,1136,1515,1541]" pageId="14" pageNumber="97" refId="ref17480" refString="PRASHAD B. 1932. - The Lamellibranchia of the Siboga Expedition. Systematic Part II. Pelecypoda (exclusive of the Pectinidae). Brill, Leiden, 353 p." type="book" year="1932">Prashad, 1932</bibRefCitation>
))
</taxonomicName>
than 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFCEFFA1AFE9B964FC81F9B7" authorityName="H. Adams &amp; A. Adams" authorityYear="1858" box="[677,793,1547,1573]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Ctenocardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="14" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCEFFA1AFE9B964FC81F9B7" box="[677,793,1547,1573]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">Ctenocardia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Finally, the presence of a second posterior lateral on the right valve is present in 
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCEFFA1A961B944FB2AF9D7" box="[1069,1202,1579,1605]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">Microfragum</emphasis>
, but less pronounced and less blade-like than in other 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFCEFFA1AFEEB905FCECF916" box="[674,884,1642,1668]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Ctenocardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="14" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCEFFA1AFEEB905FC86F916" box="[674,798,1642,1668]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">Ctenocardia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, where it forms a pocket with the anterior lateral.To formally recognize both these similarities and differences, we propose relegating 
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCFFFA0AD3FBE99FF65FD82" box="[115,253,502,528]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="98">Microfragum</emphasis>
to a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFCFFFA0AC89BE99FDDDFD82" authorityName="H. Adams &amp; A. Adams" authorityYear="1858" box="[453,581,502,528]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Ctenocardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="15" pageNumber="98" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCFFFA0AC89BE99FDDDFD82" box="[453,581,502,528]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="98">Ctenocardia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with 
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCFFFA0AD3FBD7AFF1BFDBD" box="[115,131,533,559]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="98">C</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFCFFFA0ADDDBD7AFE85FDBD" authorityName="Deshayes" authorityYear="1855" box="[145,285,533,559]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Cardium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="15" pageNumber="98" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="festivum" subGenus="Microfragum">
(
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCFFFA0ADD6BD7AFF2AFDBD" box="[154,178,533,559]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="98">M</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCFFFA0AD84BD7AFE85FDBD" box="[200,285,533,559]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="98">festivum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCFFFA0AC1DBD7AFEFBFDBD" box="[337,355,533,559]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="98">C</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFCFFFA0AC3DBD7AFD87FDBD" authority="Vidal &amp; Kirkendale, 2007" authorityName="Vidal &amp; Kirkendale" authorityYear="2007" box="[369,543,533,559]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Ctenocardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="15" pageNumber="98" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="subfestivum" status="n. sp." subGenus="Microfragum">
(
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCFFFA0AC36BD7AFE0AFDBD" box="[378,402,533,559]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="98">M</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCFFFA0ACE4BD7AFD87FDBD" box="[424,543,533,559]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="98">subfestivum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="CDB8F621FFCFFFA0AF69BD7AFDC7FDBD" box="[549,607,533,559]" pageId="15" pageNumber="98" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
the only taxa presently allied to this subgenus. “ 
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCFFFA0AF0CBD5AFF21FDFD" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="98">Microfragum</emphasis>
” 
<taxonomicName id="23FFECCBFFCFFFA0AD87BD3AFE20FDFD" authority="(Tate, 1889)" baseAuthorityName="Tate" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[203,440,597,623]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Fragum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="15" pageNumber="98" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="erugatum">
<emphasis id="D68B4B5AFFCFFFA0AD87BD3AFEB4FDFD" box="[203,300,597,623]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="98">erugatum</emphasis>
(Tate, 1889)
